nal plugins or services needed.','The image optimization service does not work on locally hosted sites or when the server is on a private network.'=>'The image optimization service does not work on locally hosted sites or when the server is on a private network.','The Critical CSS service does not work on locally hosted sites or when the server is on a private network.'=>'The Critical CSS service does not work on locally hosted sites or when the server is on a private network.','of the above rules got flagged by criticalcss.com as possibly needing review. This is often due to font-related issues which can be safely ignored, but in case of doubt do a visual test or check for Cumulative Layout Shift issues in e.g. Pagespeed Insights.'=>'of the above rules got flagged by criticalcss.com as possibly needing review. This is often due to font-related issues which can be safely ignored, but in case of doubt do a visual test or check for Cumulative Layout Shift issues in e.g. Pagespeed Insights.','Every %s (Autoptimize Crit. CSS)'=>'Every %s (Autoptimize Crit. CSS)','Path validation error:\\n\\nThe path contains characters that are not permitted, remove or encode the unsafe characters.'=>'Path validation error:\\n\\nThe path contains characters that are not permitted, remove or encode the unsafe characters.','Rule validation error:\\n\\nType based rules requires a minified critical CSS.'=>'Rule validation error:\\n\\nType based rules requires a minified critical CSS.','Rule validation error:\\n\\nBased on your rule type, you should set a path or conditional tag.'=>'Rule validation error:\\n\\nBased on your rule type, you should set a path or conditional tag.','Disable extra compatibility logic?'=>'Disable extra compatibility logic?','Enable this if you want inline JS or CSS to be minified as well.'=>'Enable this if you want inline JS or CSS to be minified as well.','Also minify inline JS/ CSS?'=>'Also minify inline JS/ CSS?','I would like be contacted about my experience with Autoptimize.'=>'I would like be contacted about my experience with Autoptimize.','Ouch, sorry about that! But almost all problems can be fixed with the right configuration, have a look at <a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2022/05/05/what-to-do-when-autoptimize-breaks-your-site/" target="_blank">this short troubleshooting howto</a> or create a topic on <a href="https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/autoptimize/#new-topic-0" target="_blank">the support forum here</a>!'=>'Ouch, sorry about that! But almost all problems can be fixed with the right configuration, have a look at <a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2022/05/05/what-to-do-when-autoptimize-breaks-your-site/" target="_blank">this short troubleshooting howto</a> or create a topic on <a href="https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/autoptimize/#new-topic-0" target="_blank">the support forum here</a>!','We would appreciate if you let us know why you\'re deactivating Autoptimize!'=>'We would appreciate if you let us know why you\'re deactivating Autoptimize!','Sorry to see you go!'=>'Sorry to see you go!','LCP Image to preload'=>'LCP Image to preload','WordPress adds block CSS and global styles to improve easy styling of block-based sites, but which can add a significant amount of CSS and SVG. If you are sure your site can do without the block CSS and "global styles", you can disable them here.'=>'WordPress adds block CSS and global styles to improve easy styling of block-based sites, but which can add a significant amount of CSS and SVG. If you are sure your site can do without the block CSS and "global styles", you can disable them here.','Remove WordPress block CSS'=>'Remove WordPress block CSS','To be able to use Critical CSS you will have to enable CSS optimization and make sure "eliminate render-blocking CSS" is active on the main Autoptimize settings page.'=>'To be able to use Critical CSS you will have to enable CSS optimization and make sure "eliminate render-blocking CSS" is active on the main Autoptimize settings page.','You can manually create rules for different types of pages or have this done fully automated on the %s tab.'=>'You can manually create rules for different types of pages or have this done fully automated on the %s tab.','Selected reason from the above survey'=>'Selected reason from the above survey','Uninstall reason'=>'Uninstall reason','Current website:'=>'Current website:','WordPress version'=>'WordPress version','Plugin version'=>'Plugin version','Below is a detailed view of all data that Optimizing Matters will receive if you fill in this survey. Your email address is only shared if you explicitly fill it in, your IP addres is never sent.'=>'Below is a detailed view of all data that Optimizing Matters will receive if you fill in this survey. Your email address is only shared if you explicitly fill it in, your IP address is never sent.','What info do we collect?'=>'What info do we collect?','Other (please specify below)'=>'Other (please specify below)','I\'m just disabling temporarily.'=>'I\'m just disabling temporarily.','I found a better solution.'=>'I found a better solution.','It broke my site.'=>'It broke my site.','As Autoptimize does not do page caching, you might have to install e.g. KeyCDN Cache Enabler or WP Super Cache as well. Feel free to create a topic on <a href="https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/autoptimize/#new-topic-0" target="_blank">the support forum here</a> to get pointers on how get the most out of Autoptimize!'=>'As Autoptimize does not do page caching, you might have to install e.g. KeyCDN Cache Enabler or WP Super Cache as well. Feel free to create a topic on <a href="https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/autoptimize/#new-topic-0" target="_blank">the support forum here</a> to get pointers on how get the most out of Autoptimize!','I don\'t see a performance improvement.'=>'I don\'t see a performance improvement.','API Key provided by a filter, no need to enter anything here.'=>'API Key provided by a filter, no need to enter anything here.','Clear CSS/ JS Cache'=>'Clear CSS/ JS Cache','CSS/ JS Cache Info'=>'CSS/ JS Cache Info','Autoptimize Pro'=>'Autoptimize Pro','Autoptimize news'=>'Autoptimize news','Enter your CDN root URL to enable CDN for Autoptimized files. The URL can be http, https or protocol-relative. This is not needed for Cloudflare.'=>'Enter your CDN root URL to enable CDN for Autoptimized files. The URL can be http, https or protocol-relative. This is not needed for Cloudflare.','example: //cdn.yoursite.com/'=>'example: //cdn.yoursite.com/','The CDN has automatically been set to make use of the image optimization CDN.'=>'The CDN has automatically been set to make use of the image optimization CDN.','Autoptimize Pro Settings'=>'Autoptimize Pro Settings','How To Use Autoptimize CriticalCSS Rules'=>'How To Use Autoptimize CriticalCSS Rules','For path based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\"'=>'For path based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\"','How To Use Autoptimize CriticalCSS Queue'=>'How To Use Autoptimize CriticalCSS Queue','Sorry, something went wrong.'=>'Sorry, something went wrong.','Could not add to CCSS job queue.'=>'Could not add to CCSS job queue.','Added to CCSS job queue.'=>'Added to CCSS job queue.','Generate Critical CSS'=>'Generate Critical CSS','It looks like you have %1$sanother plugin also doing CSS and/ or JS optimization%2$s, which can result in hard to troubleshoot %1$sconflicts%2$s. For this reason it is recommended to disable this functionality in'=>'It looks like you have %1$sanother plugin also doing CSS and/ or JS optimization%2$s, which can result in hard to troubleshoot %1$sconflicts%2$s. For this reason it is recommended to disable this functionality in','The "Eliminate render-blocking CSS" option was activated to allow critical CSS to be used.'=>'The "Eliminate render-blocking CSS" option was activated to allow critical CSS to be used.','Manually process the job queue'=>'Manually process the job queue','Could not process queue.'=>'Could not process queue.','The queue is locked, retry in a couple of minutes. If this problem persists and the queue is not moving at all remove the <code>wp-content/uploads/ao_ccss/queue.lock</code> file.'=>'The queue is locked, retry in a couple of minutes. If this problem persists and the queue is not moving at all remove the <code>wp-content/uploads/ao_ccss/queue.lock</code> file.','Queue processed, reloading page.'=>'Queue processed, reloading page.','<b>This functionality will be removed in a next major version of Autoptimize</b>, being replaced by the combination of the "do not aggregate but defer JS" + "defer inline JS" options on the main settings page.'=>'<b>This functionality will be removed in a next major version of Autoptimize</b>, being replaced by the combination of the "do not aggregate but defer JS" + "defer inline JS" options on the main settings page.','Defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files? (deprecated)'=>'Defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files? (deprecated)','Lazyload images?'=>'Lazyload images?','Inline critical CSS?'=>'Inline critical CSS?','Optimize CSS?'=>'Optimize CSS?','Optimize JS?'=>'Optimize JS?','Optimize this page?'=>'Optimize this page?','Autoptimize this page'=>'Autoptimize this page','Automatically serve AVIF image format to any browser that supports it.'=>'Automatically serve AVIF image format to any browser that supports it.','You have "defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files" active (under Advanced Settings), but that functionality is deprecated and will be removed in the next major version of Autoptimize. Consider using the new "Do not aggregate but defer" and "Also defer inline JS" options on the main settings page instead.'=>'You have "defer jQuery and other non-aggregated JS-files" active (under Advanced Settings), but that functionality is deprecated and will be removed in the next major version of Autoptimize. Consider using the new "Do not aggregate but defer" and "Also defer inline JS" options on the main settings page instead.','Add a "meta box" to the post/ page edit screen allowing different optimizations to be turned off on a per post/ page level?'=>'Add a "meta box" to the post/ page edit screen allowing different optimizations to be turned off on a per post/ page level?','Enable configuration per post/ page?'=>'Enable configuration per post/ page?','Remove Unused CSS?'=>'Remove Unused CSS?','Eliminate render-blocking CSS?'=>'Eliminate render-blocking CSS?','Autoptimize combines your theme & plugins\' JavaScript, but does not know what is used and what is not. If Google Pagespeed Insights detects unused JavaScript, consider using a plugin like "Plugin Organizer" or similar to manage what JavaScript is added where.'=>'Autoptimize combines your theme & plugins\' JavaScript, but does not know what is used and what is not. If Google Pagespeed Insights detects unused JavaScript, consider using a plugin like "Plugin Organizer" or similar to manage what JavaScript is added where.','Remove Unused JavaScript?'=>'Remove Unused JavaScript?','Important: when "aggregate JS-files" is on, excluded non-minified files are still minified by Autoptimize unless that option under "misc" is disabled.'=>'Important: when "aggregate JS-files" is on, excluded non-minified files are still minified by Autoptimize unless that option under "misc" is disabled.','A comma-separated list of scripts you do not want optimized, for example \'whatever.js, my_var\' (without the quotes).'=>'A comma-separated list of scripts you do not want optimized, for example \'whatever.js, my_var\' (without the quotes).','Also defer inline JS. Generally this will allow all JS to be deferred, so you should remove default exclusions, test and only exclude specific items if still needed.'=>'Also defer inline JS. Generally this will allow all JS to be deferred, so you should remove default exclusions, test and only exclude specific items if still needed.','Also defer inline JS?'=>'Also defer inline JS?','Individual JS-files will be minified and deferred, making them non-render-blocking.'=>'Individual JS-files will be minified and deferred, making them non-render-blocking.','If your aggregated scripts break because of a JS-error, you might want to try this, but generally discouraged.'=>'If your aggregated scripts break because of a JS-error, you might want to try this, but generally discouraged.','Load JavaScript early (discouraged as it makes the JS render blocking)'=>'Load JavaScript early (discouraged as it makes the JS render blocking)','Let Autoptimize also extract JS from the HTML (discouraged as it can make Autoptimize\'s cache size grow quickly)'=>'Let Autoptimize also extract JS from the HTML (discouraged as it can make Autoptimize\'s cache size grow quickly)','Aggregate all linked JS-files to have them loaded non-render blocking?'=>'Aggregate all linked JS-files to have them loaded non-render blocking?','you can click %1$shere to refresh your quota status%2$s'=>'you can click %1$shere to refresh your quota status%2$s','Get more Google love by speeding up your website. Start serving on-the-fly optimized images (also in the "next-gen" %4$sWebP%5$s image format) by %1$sShortPixel%2$s. No additional image optimization plugins are needed: your images are optimized, cached and served from %3$sShortPixel\'s global CDN%2$s.'=>'Get more Google love by speeding up your website. Start serving on-the-fly optimized images (also in the "next-gen" %4$sWebP%5$s image format) by %1$sShortPixel%2$s. No additional image optimization plugins are needed: your images are optimized, cached and served from %3$sShortPixel\'s global CDN%2$s.','Don\'t lazyload the first X images, \'1\' lazyloads all.'=>'Don\'t lazyload the first X images, \'1\' lazyloads all.','Lazy-load from nth image'=>'Lazy-load from nth image','Comma-separated list of image classes or filenames that should not be optimized.'=>'Comma-separated list of image classes or filenames that should not be optimized.','Optimization exclusions'=>'Optimization exclusions','Do not aggregate but defer?'=>'Do not aggregate but defer?','It looks like the amount of Critical CSS rules is very high, it is recommended to reconfigure Autoptimize (e.g. by manually creating broader rules) to ensure less rules are created.'=>'It looks like the amount of Critical CSS rules is very high, it is recommended to reconfigure Autoptimize (e.g. by manually creating broader rules) to ensure less rules are created.','In the meantime you might want to <strong>edit default rule CSS now</strong>, to avoid all CSS being inlined when no (applicable) rules are found.'=>'In the meantime you might want to <strong>edit default rule CSS now</strong>, to avoid all CSS being inlined when no (applicable) rules are found.','The cronned queue processing is an asynchronous process triggerd by (WordPress) cron. To avoid this process from running too long and potentially getting killed, you can set the number of seconds here, 0 means no limit.'=>'The cronned queue processing is an asynchronous process triggered by (WordPress) cron. To avoid this process from running too long and potentially getting killed, you can set the number of seconds here, 0 means no limit.','Queue processing time limit'=>'Queue processing time limit','If you have enough CDN quota remaining, then you may need to %1$sassociate your domain%2$s to your Shortpixel account.'=>'If you have enough CDN quota remaining, then you may need to %1$sassociate your domain%2$s to your Shortpixel account.','Enable 404 fallbacks?'=>'Enable 404 fallbacks?','In rare cases the critical CSS needs to be removed once the full CSS loads, this option makes it so!'=>'In rare cases the critical CSS needs to be removed once the full CSS loads, this option makes it so!','Unload critical CSS after page load?'=>'Unload critical CSS after page load?','Something went wrong when checking your API key, make sure you server can communicate with https://criticalcss.com and/ or try again later.'=>'Something went wrong when checking your API key, make sure you server can communicate with https://criticalcss.com and/ or try again later.','Invalid'=>'Invalid','Valid'=>'Valid','Sometimes Autoptimized JS/ CSS is referenced in cached HTML but is already removed, resulting in broken sites. With this option on, Autoptimize will try to redirect those not-found files to "fallback"-versions, keeping the page/ site somewhat intact. In some cases, this will require extra web-server level configuration to ensure %1$swp-content/autoptimize_404_handler.php%2$s is set to handle 404\'s in %1$swp-content/cache/autoptimize%2$s.'=>'Sometimes Autoptimized JS/ CSS is referenced in cached HTML but is already removed, resulting in broken sites. With this option on, Autoptimize will try to redirect those not-found files to "fallback"-versions, keeping the page/ site somewhat intact. In some cases, this will require extra web-server level configuration to ensure %1$swp-content/autoptimize_404_handler.php%2$s is set to handle 404\'s in %1$swp-content/cache/autoptimize%2$s.','Inlining all CSS is an easy way to stop the CSS from being render-blocking, but is generally not recommended because the size of the HTML increases significantly. Additionally, it might push meta-tags down to a position where e.g. Facebook and Whatsapp will not find them anymore, breaking thumbnails when sharing.'=>'Inlining all CSS is an easy way to stop the CSS from being render-blocking, but is generally not recommended because the size of the HTML increases significantly. Additionally, it might push meta-tags down to a position where e.g. Facebook and Whatsapp will not find them any more, breaking thumbnails when sharing.','Remove all rules'=>'Remove all rules','Add CSS To All Rules'=>'Add CSS To All Rules','Edit Default Rule CSS'=>'Edit Default Rule CSS','Add New Rule'=>'Add New Rule','At any time you can delete an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> or <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule by cliking on "Remove" button of the desired rule and saving your changes.'=>'At any time you can delete an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> or <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule by clicking on "Remove" button of the desired rule and saving your changes.','You can create <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rules for specific page paths (URL). Longer, more specific paths have higher priority over shorter ones, which in turn have higher priority over <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rules. Also, critical CSS files from <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are NEVER updated automatically.</strong>'=>'You can create <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rules for specific page paths (URL). Longer, more specific paths have higher priority over shorter ones, which in turn have higher priority over <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rules. Also, critical CSS files from <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are NEVER updated automatically.</strong>','If you want to make any fine tunning in the critical CSS file of an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule, click on "Edit" button of that rule, change what you need, submit and save it. The rule you\'ve just edited becomes a <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule then.'=>'If you want to make any fine tuning in the critical CSS file of an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule, click on "Edit" button of that rule, change what you need, submit and save it. The rule you\'ve just edited becomes a <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule then.','These requests also creates an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule for you. The critical CSS files from <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> when a CSS file in your theme or frontend plugins changes.'=>'These requests also creates an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule for you. The critical CSS files from <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> when a CSS file in your theme or frontend plugins changes.','Upon a request to any of the frontend pages made by a <strong>not logged in user</strong>, it will <strong>asynchronously</strong> fetch and update the critical CSS from <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for conditional tags you have on your site (e.g. is_page, is_single, is_archive etc.)'=>'Upon a request to any of the frontend pages made by a <strong>not logged in user</strong>, it will <strong>asynchronously</strong> fetch and update the critical CSS from <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for conditional tags you have on your site (e.g. is_page, is_single, is_archive etc.)','When a valid <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key is in place, Autoptimize starts to operate <strong>automatically</strong>.'=>'When a valid <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key is in place, Autoptimize starts to operate <strong>automatically</strong>.','TL;DR:<br />Critical CSS files from <span class=\'badge auto\'>AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> while from <span class=\'badge manual\'>MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are not.</strong>'=>'TL;DR:<br />Critical CSS files from <span class=\'badge auto\'>AUTO</span> <strong>rules are updated automatically</strong> while from <span class=\'badge manual\'>MANUAL</span> <strong>rules are not.</strong>','Paste your minified additional critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the CSS to be added AT THE END of every critical CSS provided by a matching rule, or the default one.'=>'Paste your minified additional critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the CSS to be added AT THE END of every critical CSS provided by a matching rule, or the default one.','Paste your minified default critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the critical CSS to be used for every page not matching any rule.'=>'Paste your minified default critical CSS here and hit submit to save. This is the critical CSS to be used for every page not matching any rule.','All Critical CSS rules will be deleted immediately and cannot be recovered.<br /><br /><strong>Are you sure?</strong>'=>'All Critical CSS rules will be deleted immediately and cannot be recovered.<br /><br /><strong>Are you sure?</strong>','Delete all Rules and Jobs'=>'Delete all Rules and Jobs','This Critical CSS rule will be deleted immediately and cannot be recovered.<br /><br /><strong>Are you sure?</strong>'=>'This Critical CSS rule will be deleted immediately and cannot be recovered.<br /><br /><strong>Are you sure?</strong>','Delete Rule'=>'Delete Rule','Paste your specific critical CSS here and hit submit to save.'=>'Paste your specific critical CSS here and hit submit to save.','Custom Critical CSS'=>'Custom Critical CSS','WooCommerce Conditional Tags'=>'WooCommerce Conditional Tags','Easy Digital Downloads Conditional Tags'=>'Easy Digital Downloads Conditional Tags','BuddyPress Conditional Tags'=>'BuddyPress Conditional Tags','BBPress Conditional Tags'=>'BBPress Conditional Tags','Page Templates'=>'Page Templates','Custom Post Types'=>'Custom Post Types','Standard Conditional Tags'=>'Standard Conditional Tags','Select from the list below...'=>'Select from the list below…','Conditional Tag, Custom Post Type or Page Template'=>'Conditional Tag, Custom Post Type or Page Template','Enter a part of the URL that identifies the page(s) you\'re targetting.'=>'Enter a part of the URL that identifies the page(s) you\'re targetting.','String in Path'=>'String in Path','Conditional Tag'=>'Conditional Tag','Path'=>'Path','Rule Type'=>'Rule Type','<strong>Rules or Queue changed!</strong> Don\'t forget to save your changes!'=>'<strong>Rules or Queue changed!</strong> Don\'t forget to save your changes!','Rules'=>'Rules','Export settings result'=>'Export settings result','WP-Cron Scheduled Events'=>'WP-Cron Scheduled Events','WP-Cron Intervals'=>'WP-Cron Intervals','Options'=>'Options','Debug Information'=>'Debug Information','Additional Critical CSS'=>'Additional Critical CSS','Default Critical CSS'=>'Default Critical CSS','Submit'=>'Submit','For path based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS here or leave this empty to fetch it from criticalcss.com and hit submit to save. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\"'=>'For path based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS here or leave this empty to fetch it from criticalcss.com and hit submit to save. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\"','For type based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS here and hit submit to save. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\".'=>'For type based rules, paste your specific and minified critical CSS here and hit submit to save. If you want to create a rule to exclude from critical CSS injection, enter \\"none\\".','Add Critical CSS Rule'=>'Add Critical CSS Rule','Loading critical CSS...'=>'Loading critical CSS…','Edit Critical CSS Rule'=>'Edit Critical CSS Rule','Delete All'=>'Delete All','Remove'=>'Remove','Edit'=>'Edit','AUTO'=>'AUTO','MANUAL'=>'MANUAL','To be fetched from criticalcss.com in the next queue run...'=>'To be fetched from criticalcss.com in the next queue run…','Critical CSS File'=>'Critical CSS File','Target'=>'Target','Type'=>'Type','Conditional Tags, Custom Post Types and Page Templates Rules'=>'Conditional Tags, Custom Post Types and Page Templates Rules','Path Based Rules'=>'Path Based Rules','<strong>CAUTION! Only use debug mode on production/live environments for ad-hoc troubleshooting and remember to turn it back off after</strong>, as this generates a lot of log-data.<br />Check the box above to enable Autoptimize CriticalCSS Power-Up debug mode. It provides debug facilities in this screen, to the browser console and to this file: '=>'<strong>CAUTION! Only use debug mode on production/live environments for ad hoc troubleshooting and remember to turn it back off after</strong>, as this generates a lot of log-data.<br />Check the box above to enable Autoptimize CriticalCSS Power-Up debug mode. It provides debug facilities in this screen, to the browser console and to this file: ','Debug Mode'=>'Debug Mode','Only requests from this domain will be sent for Critical CSS generation (pricing is per domain/ month).'=>'Only requests from this domain will be sent for Critical CSS generation (pricing is per domain/ month).','Don\'t leave this empty, put e.g. https://example.net/ or simply \'none\' to disable domain binding.'=>'Don\'t leave this empty, put e.g. https://example.net/ or simply \'none\' to disable domain binding.','Bound domain'=>'Bound domain','Defer all non-aggregated JS, including jQuery and inline JS to fix remaining render-blocking issues. Make sure to test your site thoroughly when activating this option!'=>'Defer all non-aggregated JS, including jQuery and inline JS to fix remaining render-blocking issues. Make sure to test your site thoroughly when activating this option!','By default for each page a separate rule is generated. If your pages have (semi-)identical above the fold look and feel and you want to keep the rules lean, you can disable that so one rule is created to all pages.'=>'By default for each page a separate rule is generated. If your pages have (semi-)identical above the fold look and feel and you want to keep the rules lean, you can disable that so one rule is created to all pages.','Force path-based rules to be generated for pages?'=>'Force path-based rules to be generated for pages?','Critical CSS is generated by criticalcss.com from your pages as seen by an "anonymous visitor". Disable this option if you don\'t want the "visitor" critical CSS to be used for logged in users.'=>'Critical CSS is generated by criticalcss.com from your pages as seen by an "anonymous visitor". Disable this option if you don\'t want the "visitor" critical CSS to be used for logged in users.','Add CCSS for logged in users?'=>'Add CCSS for logged in users?','In some (rare) cases the generation of critical CSS works better with the original CSS instead of the Autoptimized one, this option enables that behavior.'=>'In some (rare) cases the generation of critical CSS works better with the original CSS instead of the Autoptimized one, this option enables that behaviour.','Fetch Original CSS'=>'Fetch Original CSS','Force include CSS selectors can be used to style dynamic content that is not part of the HTML that is seen during the Critical CSS generation. To use this feature, add comma separated values with both simple strings and/or regular expressions to match the desired selectors. Regular expressions must be preceeded by two forward slashes. For instance: <code>.button-special,//#footer</code>. In this example <code>.button-special</code> will match <code>.button-special</code> selector only, while <code>//#footer</code> will match <code>#footer</code>, <code>#footer-address</code> and <code>#footer-phone</code> selectors in case they exist.<br />Do take into account that changing this setting will only affect new/ updated rules, so you might want to remove old rules and clear your page cache to expedite the forceIncludes becoming used.'=>'Force include CSS selectors can be used to style dynamic content that is not part of the HTML that is seen during the Critical CSS generation. To use this feature, add comma separated values with both simple strings and/or regular expressions to match the desired selectors. Regular expressions must be preceded by two forward slashes. For instance: <code>.button-special,//#footer</code>. In this example <code>.button-special</code> will match <code>.button-special</code> selector only, while <code>//#footer</code> will match <code>#footer</code>, <code>#footer-address</code> and <code>#footer-phone</code> selectors in case they exist.<br />Do take into account that changing this setting will only affect new/ updated rules, so you might want to remove old rules and clear your page cache to expedite the forceIncludes becoming used.','.button-special,//#footer'=>'.button-special,//#footer','Force Include CSS selectors'=>'Force Include CSS selectors','<a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> default viewport size is 1400x1080 pixels (width x height). You can change this size by typing a desired width and height values above. Allowed value ranges are from 800 to 4096 for width and from 600 to 2160 for height.'=>'<a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> default viewport size is 1400x1080 pixels (width x height). You can change this size by typing a desired width and height values above. Allowed value ranges are from 800 to 4096 for width and from 600 to 2160 for height.','Height'=>'Height','Width'=>'Width','Viewport Size'=>'Viewport Size','Advanced Settings'=>'Advanced Settings','Retry'=>'Retry','Delete all jobs?'=>'Delete all jobs?','Cancel'=>'Cancel','Delete'=>'Delete','Job status is '=>'Job status is ','N/A'=>'N/A','UNKNOWN'=>'UNKNOWN','Get Help'=>'Get Help','ERROR'=>'ERROR','DONE'=>'DONE','- Validation: '=>'- Validation: ','- Result: '=>'- Result: ','- Status: '=>'- Status: ','- Job ID: '=>'- Job ID: ','Info from criticalcss.com:'=>'Info from criticalcss.com:','REVIEW'=>'REVIEW','PENDING'=>'PENDING','None'=>'None','New'=>'New','Remove all jobs'=>'Remove all jobs','Actions'=>'Actions','Finish Date'=>'Finish Date','Creation Date'=>'Creation Date','Page Type'=>'Page Type','Page Path'=>'Page Path','Target Rule'=>'Target Rule','Status'=>'Status','<strong>A word about WordPress cron:</strong> Autoptimize watches the queue by using WordPress Cron (or WP-Cron for short.) It <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2013/10/schedule-events-using-wordpress-cron/#limitations-of-wordpress-cron-and-solutions-to-fix-em" target="_blank">could be faulty</a> on very light or very heavy loads. If your site receives just a few or thousands visits a day, it might be a good idea to <a href="https://developer.wordpress.org/plugins/cron/hooking-wp-cron-into-the-system-task-scheduler/" target="_blank">turn WP-Cron off and use your system task scheduler</a> to fire it instead.'=>'<strong>A word about WordPress cron:</strong> Autoptimize watches the queue by using WordPress Cron (or WP-Cron for short.) It <a href="https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2013/10/schedule-events-using-wordpress-cron/#limitations-of-wordpress-cron-and-solutions-to-fix-em" target="_blank">could be faulty</a> on very light or very heavy loads. If your site receives just a few or thousands visits a day, it might be a good idea to <a href="https://developer.wordpress.org/plugins/cron/hooking-wp-cron-into-the-system-task-scheduler/" target="_blank">turn WP-Cron off and use your system task scheduler</a> to fire it instead.','To get more information about jobs statuses, specially the ones with <span class="badge error">E</span> and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> status, hover your mouse in the status badge of that job. This information might be crucial when contacting <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.'=>'To get more information about jobs statuses, specially the ones with <span class="badge error">E</span> and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> status, hover your mouse in the status badge of that job. This information might be crucial when contacting <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.','Sometimes an unknown condition can happen. In this case, the job status becomes <span class="badge unknown">U</span> and you may want to ask <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for help or just delete it.'=>'Sometimes an unknown condition can happen. In this case, the job status becomes <span class="badge unknown">U</span> and you may want to ask <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for help or just delete it.','When things go wrong, a job is marked as <span class="badge error">E</span>. You can retry faulty jobs, delete them or get in touch with <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.'=>'When things go wrong, a job is marked as <span class="badge error">E</span>. You can retry faulty jobs, delete them or get in touch with <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> for assistance.','As soon as <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> returns a valid critical CSS file, the job is then finished and removed from the queue.'=>'As soon as <a href="https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> returns a valid critical CSS file, the job is then finished and removed from the queue.','Autoptimize constantly queries the queue for <span class=\'badge new\'>N</span> jobs. When it finds one, gears spins and jobs becomes <span class=\'badge pending\'>P</span> while they are running and <a href=\'https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1\' target=\'_blank\'>criticalcss.com</a> doesn\'t return a result.'=>'Autoptimize constantly queries the queue for <span class=\'badge new\'>N</span> jobs. When it finds one, gears spins and jobs becomes <span class=\'badge pending\'>P</span> while they are running and <a href=\'https://criticalcss.com/?aff=1\' target=\'_blank\'>criticalcss.com</a> doesn\'t return a result.','When the conditions to create a job are met (i.e. user not logged in, no matching <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule or CSS files has changed for an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule), a <span class="badge new">N</span> job is created in the queue.'=>'When the conditions to create a job are met (i.e. user not logged in, no matching <span class="badge manual">MANUAL</span> rule or CSS files has changed for an <span class="badge auto">AUTO</span> rule), a <span class="badge new">N</span> job is created in the queue.','The queue operates <strong>automatically, asynchronously and on regular intervals of 10 minutes.</strong> To view updated queue status, refresh this page.'=>'The queue operates <strong>automatically, asynchronously and on regular intervals of 10 minutes.</strong> To view updated queue status, refresh this page.','TL;DR:<br /><strong>Queue runs every 10 minutes.</strong> Job statuses are <span class="badge new">N</span> for NEW, <span class="badge pending">P</span> for PENDING, <span class="badge error">E</span> for ERROR and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> for UNKOWN.'=>'TL;DR:<br /><strong>Queue runs every 10 minutes.</strong> Job statuses are <span class="badge new">N</span> for NEW, <span class="badge pending">P</span> for PENDING, <span class="badge error">E</span> for ERROR and <span class="badge unknown">U</span> for UNKOWN.','Click the side arrow to toggle instructions'=>'Click the side arrow to toggle instructions','This will delete all jobs, are you sure?'=>'This will delete all jobs, are you sure?','Delete all jobs'=>'Delete all jobs','Are you sure you want to delete this job?'=>'Are you sure you want to delete this job?','Delete Job'=>'Delete Job','Are you sure you want to retry this job?'=>'Are you sure you want to retry this job?','Retry Job'=>'Retry Job','Job Queue'=>'Job Queue','Enter your <a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key above. The key is revalidated every time a new job is sent to it.<br />To obtain your API key, go to <a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> > Account > API Keys.<br />Requests to generate a critical CSS via the API are priced at £5 per domain per month.<br /><strong>Not sure yet? With the <a href="https://criticalcss.com/faq/?aff=1#trial" target="_blank">30 day money back guarantee</a>, you have nothing to lose!</strong>'=>'Enter your <a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> API key above. The key is revalidated every time a new job is sent to it.<br />To obtain your API key, go to <a href="https://criticalcss.com/account/api-keys?aff=1" target="_blank">criticalcss.com</a> > Account > API Keys.<br />Requests to generate a critical CSS via the API are priced at £5 per domain per month.<br /><strong>Not sure yet? With the <a href="https://criticalcss.com/faq/?aff=1#trial" target="_blank">30 day money back guarantee</a>, you have nothing to lose!</strong>','Please enter your criticalcss.com API key here.'=>'Please enter your criticalcss.com API key here.','Your API Key'=>'Your API Key','API Key'=>'API Key','API key provided by your host/ WordPress administrator, no need to enter anything here. In case of problems with the API key, contact your host/ WordPress administrator.'=>'API key provided by your host/ WordPress administrator, no need to enter anything here. In case of problems with the API key, contact your host/ WordPress administrator.','Import Settings'=>'Import Settings','Export Settings'=>'Export Settings','<p>Critical CSS settings cannot be set at network level as critical CSS is specific to each sub-site.</p><p>You can however provide the critical CSS API key for use by all sites by adding this your wp-config.php as %s</p>'=>'<p>Critical CSS settings cannot be set at network level as critical CSS is specific to each sub-site.</p><p>You can however provide the critical CSS API key for use by all sites by adding this your wp-config.php as %s</p>','The critical CSS service has been reported to be down. Although no new rules will be created for now, this does not prevent existing rules from being applied.'=>'The critical CSS service has been reported to be down. Although no new rules will be created for now, this does not prevent existing rules from being applied.','Great, Autoptimize will now automatically start creating new critical CSS rules, you should see those appearing below in the next couple of hours.'=>'Great, Autoptimize will now automatically start creating new critical CSS rules, you should see those appearing below in the next couple of hours.','It looks like there might be a problem with WordPress cron (task scheduling). Have a look at <a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2023/03/17/how-to-fix-autoptimize-critical-css-cron-issue/" target="_blank">the FAQ</a> or the info in the Job Queue instructions if all jobs remain in "N" status and no rules are created.'=>'It looks like there might be a problem with WordPress cron (task scheduling). Have a look at <a href="https://blog.futtta.be/2023/03/17/how-to-fix-autoptimize-critical-css-cron-issue/" target="_blank">the FAQ</a> or the info in the Job Queue instructions if all jobs remain in "N" status and no rules are created.','Could not create the required directory. Make sure the webserver can write to the wp-content/uploads directory.'=>'Could not create the required directory. Make sure the webserver can write to the wp-content/uploads directory.','Comma-separated list with full URL\'s of to to-be-preloaded resources. To be used sparingly!'=>'Comma-separated list with full URLs of to to-be-preloaded resources. To be used sparingly!','Preload specific requests (advanced users)'=>'Preload specific requests (advanced users)','includes %1$sdisplay:swap%2$s.'=>'includes %1$sdisplay:swap%2$s.','Critical CSS'=>'Critical CSS','By default Autoptimize is also active for logged-on editors/ administrators, uncheck this option if you don\'t want Autoptimize to optimize when logged in e.g. to use a page builder.'=>'By default Autoptimize is also active for logged-on editors/ administrators, uncheck this option if you don\'t want Autoptimize to optimize when logged in e.g. to use a page builder.','Also optimize for logged in editors/ administrators?'=>'Also optimize for logged in editors/ administrators?','Paste the above the fold CSS here. You can leave this empty when using the automated Critical CSS integration.'=>'Paste the above the fold CSS here. You can leave this empty when using the automated Critical CSS integration.','Important: excluded non-minified files are still minified by Autoptimize unless that option under "misc" is disabled.'=>'Important: excluded non-minified files are still minified by Autoptimize unless that option under "misc" is disabled.','Enable Autoptimize configuration per site.'=>'Enable Autoptimize configuration per site.','Enable site configuration?'=>'Enable site configuration?','Multisite Options'=>'Multisite Options','Autoptimize is enabled and configured on a WordPress network level. Please contact your network administrator if you need Autoptimize settings changed.'=>'Autoptimize is enabled and configured on a WordPress network level. Please contact your network administrator if you need Autoptimize settings changed.','It seems ShortPixel image optimization is not able to fetch images from your site, %1$scheck the documentation here%2$s for more information'=>'It seems ShortPixel image optimization is not able to fetch images from your site, %1$scheck the documentation here%2$s for more information','Only works for websites and images that are publicly available.'=>'Only works for websites and images that are publicly available.','JS, CSS  &amp; HTML'=>'JS, CSS  &amp; HTML','When aggregating JS or CSS, excluded files that are not minified (based on filename) are by default minified by Autoptimize despite being excluded. Uncheck this option if anything breaks despite excluding.'=>'When aggregating JS or CSS, excluded files that are not minified (based on filename) are by default minified by Autoptimize despite being excluded. Uncheck this option if anything breaks despite excluding.','Minify excluded CSS and JS files?'=>'Minify excluded CSS and JS files?','Comma-separated list of to be excluded image classes or filenames.'=>'Comma-separated list of to be excluded image classes or filenames.','Lazy-load exclusions'=>'Lazy-load exclusions','Image lazy-loading will delay the loading of non-visible images to allow the browser to optimally load all resources for the "above the fold"-page first.'=>'Image lazy-loading will delay the loading of non-visible images to allow the browser to optimally load all resources for the "above the fold"-page first.','Lazy-load images?'=>'Lazy-load images?','Load AVIF in supported browsers?'=>'Load AVIF in supported browsers?','Image optimization'=>'Image optimization','Please %1$sdisable Jetpack\'s site accelerator for images%2$s to be able to use Autoptomize\'s advanced image optimization features below.'=>'Please %1$sdisable Jetpack\'s site accelerator for images%2$s to be able to use Autoptomize\'s advanced image optimization features below.','Images'=>'Images','Makes your site faster by optimizing CSS, JS, Images, Google fonts and more.'=>'Makes your site faster by optimizing CSS, JS, Images, Google Fonts and more.','based on previously fetched data'=>'based on previously fetched data','based on status at '=>'based on status at ','Did you know that Autoptimize offers on-the-fly image optimization (with support for WebP and AVIF) and CDN via ShortPixel? Check out the %1$sAutoptimize Image settings%2$s to enable this option.'=>'Did you know that Autoptimize offers on-the-fly image optimization (with support for WebP and AVIF) and CDN via ShortPixel? Check out the %1$sAutoptimize Image settings%2$s to enable this option.','You have "Async JavaScript" installed, %1$sconfiguration of async javascript is best done there%2$s.'=>'